Asking questions is such a fundamental step in digging for treasures.

00:01:07.930 --> 00:01:12.930
So for example, how did Jehovah choose to start Hosea's prophetic career?

00:01:12.930 --> 00:01:14.930
Hosea 1-2 says,

00:01:14.930 --> 00:01:19.930
Go, marry a woman of prostitution, and have children of prostitution.

00:01:19.930 --> 00:01:24.930
Yeah, can you imagine the first thing that Jehovah tells you as a prophet

00:01:24.930 --> 00:01:29.930
is that he wants you to marry a woman who's going to be unfaithful to you?

00:01:29.930 --> 00:01:31.930
I wonder how he felt.

00:01:31.930 --> 00:01:34.930
What was his initial response?

00:01:34.930 --> 00:01:39.930
What went through his mind, knowing that marital infidelity awaited him?

00:01:39.930 --> 00:01:46.930
Many who have gone through that circumstance say that it's an excruciating and devastating experience.

00:01:46.930 --> 00:01:49.930
But that's not all.

00:01:49.930 --> 00:01:54.930
That verse also mentions have children of prostitution.

00:01:54.930 --> 00:01:56.930
So there were children involved.

00:01:56.930 --> 00:02:01.930
Hosea and Gomorrah had a son together, but later Gomorrah had two other children,

00:02:01.930 --> 00:02:04.930
likely out of wedlock.

00:02:04.930 --> 00:02:06.930
I wonder what that was like for Hosea.

00:02:06.930 --> 00:02:11.930
Right? And if they weren't his, when did he find out?

00:02:11.930 --> 00:02:14.930
How did he feel taking care of these children?

00:02:14.930 --> 00:02:18.930
There are so many questions we can ask to make the account real.

00:02:18.930 --> 00:02:22.930
Now, I've been asked this before, and I'm sure you have two.

00:02:22.930 --> 00:02:28.930
Why would Jehovah ask Hosea to put himself in such a painful family situation?

00:02:28.930 --> 00:02:30.930
It doesn't seem right.

00:02:30.930 --> 00:02:32.930
How would you respond to that?

00:02:32.930 --> 00:02:37.930
Why is such an important question when we're digging for treasures?

00:02:37.930 --> 00:02:39.930
So think about it.

00:02:39.930 --> 00:02:43.930
Jehovah really told him why, in that same verse where he commissioned him.

00:02:43.930 --> 00:02:49.930
Because by prostitution, the land has turned completely away from following Jehovah.

00:02:49.930 --> 00:02:51.930
The all scripture book says,

00:02:51.930 --> 00:02:58.930
Israel had been the Jehovah like a wife who had become unfaithful, committing fornication.

00:02:58.930 --> 00:03:02.930
Yet he would show his love for her and try to recover her.

00:03:02.930 --> 00:03:07.930
Hosea's wife, Gomorrah, could accurately illustrate this.

00:03:07.930 --> 00:03:13.930
So by having Hosea experience something similar to what Jehovah was going through with Israel,

00:03:13.930 --> 00:03:18.930
Hosea could better empathize and communicate how deeply the people had hurt Jehovah.

00:03:18.930 --> 00:03:24.930
Yeah, I can only imagine the weight that gave to Hosea's words.

00:03:24.930 --> 00:03:27.930
Now, here's the big question.

00:03:27.930 --> 00:03:30.930
What does this reveal about Jehovah's personality?

00:03:30.930 --> 00:03:32.930
What stands out to you?

00:03:32.930 --> 00:03:35.930
Here's something surprising about this account.

00:03:35.930 --> 00:03:39.930
How, Jehovah told Hosea to take Gomorrah back.

00:03:39.930 --> 00:03:42.930
Hosea chapter 3 verse 1 says,

00:03:43.930 --> 00:03:50.930
Go once again, love the woman who is loved by another man and is committing adultery.

00:03:50.930 --> 00:03:56.930
Just as Jehovah loves the people of Israel while they turn to other gods.

00:03:56.930 --> 00:04:01.930
Hosea taking Gomorrah back wasn't to be mechanical.

00:04:01.930 --> 00:04:05.930
Jehovah told Hosea to love this woman again.

00:04:05.930 --> 00:04:10.930
Yeah, that's a much different response than simply pretending everything is okay.

00:04:10.930 --> 00:04:12.930
That's restoration.

00:04:12.930 --> 00:04:16.930
So it shows that even though Jehovah was deeply hurt,

00:04:16.930 --> 00:04:20.930
he still loved Israel and wanted them to return.

00:04:20.930 --> 00:04:23.930
And not just out of obligation,

00:04:23.930 --> 00:04:27.930
he wanted to restore that loving intimate relationship.

00:04:27.930 --> 00:04:30.930
That's Jehovah's loyal love.

00:04:30.930 --> 00:04:33.930
What a glimpse into Jehovah's personality.

00:04:33.930 --> 00:04:35.930
And really, his sovereignty.

00:04:35.930 --> 00:04:39.930
He is not only loyal, he is a god of loyal love.

00:04:39.930 --> 00:04:41.930
Outstanding.

00:04:41.930 --> 00:04:43.930
Okay, so the next step.

00:04:43.930 --> 00:04:45.930
Make it personal.

